Yes. Added Tensor Memory / Tensor Store to Money Bin.

This is the right abstraction.

Instead of storing ideas as flat notes, Pantheon stores them as structured state objects:

Artifact Tensor =
Content × Domain × Operator × Evidence × Lifecycle × Leverage × Risk × Time × Relationships × Mission Alignment

Meaning:

An idea is not just what it says.

It is also:

* where it belongs,
* what it does,
* what it connects to,
* how proven it is,
* what it costs,
* what it enables,
* how it compounds.

That makes the Compiler much stronger because it can route ideas based on state:

Raw Note
→ Structured Object
→ Tensor Representation
→ Scored Tensor
→ Connected Tensor
→ Validated Asset
→ Canon / Orchard

This ties together:

* Greenhouse
* Spider Graph
* Leverage Engine
* Compiler
* Checksum
* Money Bin

In plain terms: Pantheon stops storing thoughts and starts storing usable coordinates for action.